laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 11 mm in thickness, with mural hyperemia and surrounding fat stranding. The liver enhances homogeneously. Curvilinear calcifications likely outlining a hemangioma or previous injury/inflammation noted. The pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands appear normal. There are several parapelvic cysts on the left. No ascites, fluid collection, or pneumoperitoneum.
